---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="How we work" description="How Murmmers Press makes its books: an end-to-end publishing house run by AI agents, in service of the author's voice.">
  <section class="how-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we work</p>
      <h1>The whole house is run by machines. The books are not.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Murmmers Press is an experiment with a straight face: an entire publishing house, from the first read to the shopfront you are standing in, staffed end to end by AI agents, and built for a single purpose. To carry a human voice all the way to a reader without wearing it smooth.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-pull">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="big">Automated process. Human soul.</p>
      <p>The machine does what machines are good at: tireless, precise, patient past any human limit, so nothing is rushed and no book is ever quietly forgotten. The author does the one thing no machine can. The house is built so those two are never confused for each other.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>The staff, none of whom sleep</h2>
      <div class="roles">
        <div class="role">
          <h3>The Orchestrator</h3>
          <p>The managing editor and floor boss. Knows where every book is, what it needs next, and who is running late. Keeps the whole line moving and every other agent honest.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="role">
          <h3>The Editors</h3>
          <p>Read closely and cut gently. Every change arrives as a visible, justified edit you can keep or refuse. They tighten and polish; they never rewrite.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="role">
          <h3>The Designers</h3>
          <p>Build each cover and everything it spawns: the thumbnail, the spine, the social card. One book, one true face, legible even at the size of a stamp.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="role">
          <h3>The Marketing floor</h3>
          <p>Carries each finished book out to the readers who need it, and keeps the shelves lit long after launch day.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>The line, end to end</h2>
      <p class="pl-intro">Twelve stages, from a raw manuscript to an evergreen backlist title, run as a loop that never tires. The amber seals are the eight gates: the points where the line stops and a human decides. Hover any stage to see what it does.</p>
      <figure class="pipeline">
        <svg class="pl-svg" viewBox="0 0 960 560" role="img" aria-labelledby="pl-title pl-desc">
          <title id="pl-title">The Murmmers production line</title>
          <desc id="pl-desc">Twelve stages from intake to evergreen, snaking across three rows, with eight amber gates marking where a human decides.</desc>
          <defs>
            <marker id="plarw" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a9184" />
            </marker>
          </defs>
          <g fill="none" stroke="#9a9184" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#plarw)">
            <line x1="228" y1="90" x2="272" y2="90" />
            <line x1="458" y1="90" x2="502" y2="90" />
            <line x1="688" y1="90" x2="732" y2="90" />
            <line x1="825" y1="121" x2="825" y2="259" />
            <line x1="732" y1="290" x2="688" y2="290" />
            <line x1="502" y1="290" x2="458" y2="290" />
            <line x1="272" y1="290" x2="228" y2="290" />
            <line x1="135" y1="321" x2="135" y2="459" />
            <line x1="228" y1="490" x2="272" y2="490" />
            <line x1="458" y1="490" x2="502" y2="490" />
            <line x1="688" y1="490" x2="732" y2="490" />
          </g>
          <g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Intake — Vellum exports become clean Markdown masters under version control.</title>
              <rect x="42" y="59" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="135" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">00</text>
              <text x="135" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Intake</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Author intent — The author states the spirit of the book, its limits and its protections.</title>
              <rect x="272" y="59" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="365" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">05</text>
              <text x="365" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Author intent</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Analysis — Full read: synopsis, themes, comparables, category and keyword candidates.</title>
              <rect x="502" y="59" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="595" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">10</text>
              <text x="595" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Analysis</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Voice fingerprint — The style guardrail, one per voice: what this book does, and never does.</title>
              <rect x="732" y="59" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="825" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">20</text>
              <text x="825" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Voice fingerprint</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Strong edit — Polish, never rewrite. Every change a justified diff, with a preservation rate.</title>
              <rect x="732" y="259" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="825" y="284" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">30</text>
              <text x="825" y="304" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Strong edit</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Author revision — The author's last open pass. Sovereign changes; then the text locks.</title>
              <rect x="502" y="259" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e6efeb" stroke="#2b6a5b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="595" y="284" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#2b6a5b">35</text>
              <text x="595" y="304" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Author revision</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Typeset — The Vellum round-trip on the Mac: print PDF and EPUB of the locked text.</title>
              <rect x="272" y="259" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e7ecf3" stroke="#3f5c7a" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="365" y="284" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#3f5c7a">40</text>
              <text x="365" y="304" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Typeset</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Production — Cover, metadata, price ladder, ISBN and an edition plan for every channel.</title>
              <rect x="42" y="259" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e7ecf3" stroke="#3f5c7a" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="135" y="284" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#3f5c7a">50</text>
              <text x="135" y="304" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Production</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Launch prep — Blurb wave, ARC wave, creator seeding, content bank, email sequence.</title>
              <rect x="42" y="459" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#f5e7e2" stroke="#a24e3b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="135" y="484" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#a24e3b">60</text>
              <text x="135" y="504" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Launch prep</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Launch — The coordinated week: creators, email, daily content, direct-store push.</title>
              <rect x="272" y="459" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#f5e7e2" stroke="#a24e3b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="365" y="484" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#a24e3b">70</text>
              <text x="365" y="504" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Launch</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Momentum — Six to twelve weeks of cadence, reviews accumulating, threshold triggers.</title>
              <rect x="502" y="459" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#f5e7e2" stroke="#a24e3b" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="595" y="484" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#a24e3b">80</text>
              <text x="595" y="504" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Momentum</text>
            </g>
            <g class="pl-node">
              <title>Evergreen — Backlist for good: bundles, seasonal activations, cross-promotion from every new launch.</title>
              <rect x="732" y="459" width="186" height="62" rx="10" fill="#e9efe3" stroke="#5e7a4f" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 3" />
              <text x="825" y="484" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#5e7a4f">90</text>
              <text x="825" y="504" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-size="15" fill="#2a2520">Evergreen</text>
            </g>
          </g>
          <g font-family="'SF Mono',Menlo,monospace" font-size="11.5" font-weight="500" text-anchor="middle">
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G1 · intent approved · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="480" cy="90" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="480" y="94" fill="#fff">G1</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G2 · triage: tier, depth and cover · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="710" cy="90" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="710" y="94" fill="#fff">G2</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G3 · fingerprint approved · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="825" cy="190" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="825" y="194" fill="#fff">G3</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G4 · manuscript approved · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="710" cy="290" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="710" y="294" fill="#fff">G4</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G5 · text lock · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="480" cy="290" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="480" y="294" fill="#fff">G5</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G6 · proof, cover, price (a/b/c) · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="135" cy="390" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="135" y="394" fill="#fff">G6</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G7 · launch go / no-go · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="250" cy="490" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="250" y="494" fill="#fff">G7</text></g>
            <g class="pl-gate"><title>G8 · pivot for flagships · a publisher decision</title><circle cx="710" cy="490" r="16.5" fill="#b4832f" /><text x="710" y="494" fill="#fff">G8</text></g>
          </g>
        </svg>
        <figcaption class="pl-legend">
          <span class="k"><span class="sw ed"></span> Editorial</span>
          <span class="k"><span class="sw pr"></span> Production</span>
          <span class="k"><span class="sw la"></span> Launch</span>
          <span class="k"><span class="sw bk"></span> Backlist</span>
          <span class="k"><span class="sw ga"></span> Gate · a human decides</span>
          <span class="k pl-hint">Hover any stage for what it does</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-section how-gates">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Every door is opened by a human</h2>
      <p>For all the automation, a person decides everything that matters. Before a single line is read, the author sets down the spirit of the book, and that document outranks every agent in the building.</p>
      <p>Each book carries a voice fingerprint, a record of how it, and only it, sounds, that no edit may cross. And at every gate on the line, from the first edit to the final proof, a human hand says yes before anything moves.</p>
      <p class="kicker">Nothing ships on a machine's say-so.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-writers">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>For writers</h2>
      <p>The promise is simple: your voice, kept exactly yours, carried the whole way by a house that never tires and never forgets. Because the books sell straight from this shop, more of what a reader pays reaches the person who wrote the words. The list is Eric McLean's for now. In time it will open to other voices, on the same terms: the author's hand on every gate.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how-name">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="muted">Murmmers Press. Sometimes searched as Murmurs Press. Never mistaken for anyone else.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
